Mouse Keys Mode v3 You can move mouse pointer by d+ijkl keys. Move pointer by: * Left: D down -> J down -> J up * Down: D down -> K down -> K up * Up: D down -> I down -> I up * Right: D down -> L down -> L up ─────────────────────────────────────── The ijkl keys also act as mouse keys when you hold d+ijkl keys down. (You can adjust timeout by "__BlockUntilKeyUp__ Timeout" in Parameters tab. ─────────────────────────────────────── To scroll: U(left) O(right) H(up) N(down). ─────────────────────────────────────── Use A key to increase speed. ("A"ccelerdte) * D+A+IJKL: High-speed movement. * D+A+UOHN: High-speed scroll wheel. ─────────────────────────────────────── Click by: Left click: D+M or D+F Middle click: D+/ or D+V Right click: D+P or D+S Button 4: D+; or D+G Button 5: D+' or D+B ─────────────────────────────────────── Warp cursor position: * D+.: Move mouse cursor to the center of the frontmost app's window. remap.mouse_keys_mode_3
